1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,088
[Marcus] <i>These illegal firearms</i>
<i>are sold everywhere.</i>

2
00:00:05,171 --> 00:00:07,465
<i>Even ordinary citizens can obtain them.</i>

3
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:09,676
[Lara] <i>And that’s exactly why</i>
<i>gun-related violence and crime</i>

4
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:10,969
<i>are on the rise.</i>

5
00:00:11,052 --> 00:00:12,512
- [Marcus] <i>We must stop this epidemic.</i>
- [gunshot]

6
00:00:12,595 --> 00:00:13,513
[tense music]

7
00:00:13,596 --> 00:00:15,390
[Theresa] <i>I already lost one son.</i>

8
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:16,725
[Marcus] <i>I'm being careful.</i>

9
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:18,935
I'll be okay. I can take care of myself.

10
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:20,937
[man] <i>Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

11
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:22,564
[Lara] <i>He has been working</i>
<i>with a gun-smuggling syndicate</i>

12
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:23,481
<i>for decades.</i>

13
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:26,484
<i>He has perfected a system</i>
<i>to evade investigations.</i>

14
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:30,030
[Azuelo] <i>Our mission</i>
<i>is to capture and arrest</i>

15
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:31,448
<i>Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

16
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:33,992
[Felix] <i>There are no civilians there!</i>
<i>You’re walking into an ambush!</i>

17
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:36,411
[Rahman] We're under attack!

18
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:38,288
[grunts]

19
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:42,625
[Jalil] <i>We are living in peace,</i>
<i>and you chose to invade our land!</i>

20
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:44,836
[Marcus] <i>We're only here</i>
<i>for Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

21
00:00:44,919 --> 00:00:48,298
[Jalil] <i>Long live! Long live!</i>

22
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,008
[loud explosion]

23
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:53,678
[Marcus] <i>You, Datu Rahman Abubakar,</i>
<i>are under arrest</i>

24
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:57,640
<i>for violating Republic Act 10591.</i>

25
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:00,393
Kah, Amah needs you.

26
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:02,979
Wake up, Kah… [sobs]

27
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:04,773
[Marcus] <i>Someone hijacked our comms.</i>

28
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:06,399
A lot of innocent people died!

29
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:08,651
[Marcus] <i>Harold was left behind,</i>
<i>and now he’s dead!</i>

30
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,611
<i>Don't you care?!</i>

31
00:01:09,694 --> 00:01:12,322
[Felix] <i>I'll deal with Marcus.</i>
<i>Consider it done.</i>

32
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:13,948
[Jamilah] <i>I will go after Amah.</i>

33
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:16,493
<i>I can't just sit here and do nothing.</i>

34
00:01:16,576 --> 00:01:18,495
<i>I have to save him.</i>

35
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:20,580
[Rahman] <i>Your allegations</i>
<i>against me are not true!</i>

36
00:01:20,663 --> 00:01:23,416
<i>You arrested me,</i>
<i>paraded me like an animal,</i>

37
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,668
<i>yet you’re the ones</i>
<i>who slaughtered children,</i>

38
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:28,254
women, and the defenseless.

39
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:31,090
So who is the real criminal?

40
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:34,135
[Azuelo] <i>You’re tarnishing</i>
<i>the agency’s name!</i>

41
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:35,970
Something went wrong during the mission.

42
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:38,014
[Azuelo] <i>I don't need your explanation!</i>

43
00:01:40,016 --> 00:01:43,228
[sobbing]

44
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:46,231
[Jamilah] <i>Kah?</i>

45
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:53,571
[mysterious theme music playing]

46
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:03,832
It was a peaceful island…

47
00:02:05,416 --> 00:02:06,751
full of civilians.

48
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,128
[tense music]

49
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:10,588
[indistinct chatter]

50
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:12,423
- The odd one is… it!
- The odd one is… it!

51
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:13,883
You're it!

52
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,094
They were celebrating when we arrived.

53
00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:21,724
Suddenly, someone spoke on the radio.

54
00:02:24,185 --> 00:02:25,353
On the national comms.

55
00:02:26,062 --> 00:02:27,564
[unknown male voice] <i>Neutralize the area.</i>

56
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:28,940
<i>There are no civilians there.</i>

57
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:30,817
<i>You’re walking into an ambush!</i>

58
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,861
"Neutralize the area.

59
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:34,904
There are no civilians there."

60
00:02:36,906 --> 00:02:39,325
That’s when the gunfire started.

61
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:41,119
[rapid gunfire]

62
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,747
I know it didn’t come from my team.

63
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:49,460
It didn't come from the islanders either.

64
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,379
What do you mean?

65
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,340
The whole thing was a setup?

66
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:56,926
Yes.

67
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:00,346
It was meant to wipe out the islanders.

68
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:04,267
As a result, we lost Rustia.

69
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:08,062
And three of my men
were left in critical condition.

70
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:12,317
[Rustia] Who would do that?

71
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:16,696
I don't know, sir.

72
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,157
But…

73
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:23,286
only someone among us
could have hijacked the comms.

74
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:25,622
- [official] What are you insinuating?
- That’s preposterous!

75
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:27,332
That is a serious allegation.

76
00:03:27,415 --> 00:03:29,083
[Gonzalez] Who are you saying did it?

77
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:33,004
How dare you accuse your own people?

78
00:03:33,087 --> 00:03:38,927
[tense music playing]

79
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:45,850
[Suarez] Sir…

80
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:49,771
I didn't hear that order, sir.

81
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:51,940
I was far from Sir Marcus.

82
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:53,316
All I heard was a gunshot.

83
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:54,484
[gunshot]

84
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:57,445
Then bullets started raining down on us.

85
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:00,615
We retaliated.

86
00:04:00,698 --> 00:04:01,658
[Felix] What?

87
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:03,326
Someone gave an order?

88
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:07,413
I'm sorry, but I didn't
hear anything, sir.

89
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,958
With all the gunfire,

90
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,542
we were under attack.

91
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:17,757
[tense music continues]

92
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:22,387
Agent Lara Angeles,

93
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:24,681
let's settle this once and for all.

94
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:29,894
Did you hear an order
to neutralize the whole village?

95
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:36,776
Agent Lara Angeles.

96
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:38,444
Answer the question for the record.

97
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:41,906
[tense music continues]

98
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:44,909
No.

99
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,621
I didn’t hear such an order

100
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:50,540
while I was monitoring
the communications line.

101
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:53,710
- But--
- That's all, Agent Angeles.

102
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:04,929
[tense music continues]

103
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:14,022
[grim music playing]

104
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,942
You know what's best for you.

105
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:20,028
- With all due respect…
- Get out of my sight this instant.

106
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:21,446
Director, I swear with all due respect,

107
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:22,363
I just want to know

108
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:23,698
why you’re trying to frame
Marcus as the bad guy.

109
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:25,825
What he said could be true.

110
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:28,119
The body cam footage really is missing.

111
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:29,579
So is the drone's footage.

112
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,248
Are you insane?

113
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,083
You want to destroy the entire agency

114
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:36,627
just to cover up your friend’s failure?

115
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:40,631
Do you not see the protesters outside?

116
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:42,467
They want answers.

117
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:45,011
So how can we give them answers
if we keep avoiding the questions?

118
00:05:46,345 --> 00:05:47,930
Enough of this drama.

119
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,932
This country needs closure.

120
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:51,434
No, you and I both know

121
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:52,852
that what this country wants
is someone to blame.

122
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:54,937
And you’re letting Marcus
take the fall for it.

123
00:05:55,563 --> 00:05:57,899
Get out of my sight, young lady.

124
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,276
Before you get dragged into this mess.

125
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:06,574
[grim music continues]

126
00:06:10,244 --> 00:06:12,830
Sorry, but I know nothing
about the order you received.

127
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:16,125
You don't have to lie for me.

128
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:20,713
But you still defended me, so thank you.

129
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:22,215
Don't mention it.

130
00:06:22,298 --> 00:06:24,008
I just did it because it was
the right thing to do.

131
00:06:26,844 --> 00:06:30,056
You don't have to ruin
yourself for me, Lara.

132
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:32,100
I know you, Marcus.

133
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:35,728
You’d do the same for me.

134
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:39,107
Damn that Felix.

135
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:40,650
Huh?

136
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:42,360
It was Felix.

137
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:44,904
He was the first to open fire.

138
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:48,074
He broke protocol,
and now he’s mocking me.

139
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,076
That bastard.

140
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:53,955
Do you think Oliver’s awake already?

141
00:06:54,038 --> 00:06:55,957
He can verify what you’re saying.

142
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,962
- [sighs]
- [phone ringing]

143
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:03,798
Hello?

144
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,341
[woman] <i>Hi, Sir Marcus.</i>

145
00:07:05,424 --> 00:07:07,135
<i>This is S. Trinidad Memorial Center.</i>

146
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:11,305
<i>I'm here to inform you that</i>
<i>Agent Oliver Lapeña is now awake.</i>

147
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,017
Okay. Uh, I'm on my way.

148
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:19,313
Go ahead. I got it here.

149
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:25,236
[suspenseful music playing]

150
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:31,951
Yes, sir.

151
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:32,910
[gasps]

152
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:34,120
I heard it.

153
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:36,664
Clearly.

154
00:07:37,623 --> 00:07:39,208
Someone gave us the order.

155
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:44,505
[breathes heavily]

156
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:46,132
Then the gunfire started.

157
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:47,884
[gunshots]

158
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,427
[Oliver] <i>They've opened fire, sir!</i>

159
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:54,056
Bodies started dropping, one by one.

160
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:57,602
- [gunshots]
- [people screaming in fear]

161
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:00,646
But the shots weren't coming
from our side, sir.

162
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:05,943
[gloomy music playing]

163
00:08:08,946 --> 00:08:10,990
[sighs deeply]

164
00:08:15,077 --> 00:08:16,579
But no one believes me.

165
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:19,081
[Oliver] Don't worry, sir.

166
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:21,167
Me.

167
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:24,295
I'll corroborate what you said.

168
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:27,006
[gloomy music continues]

169
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:30,343
You need to regain your strength first.

170
00:08:30,426 --> 00:08:31,844
Don't think about me, sir.

171
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:33,763
I'm fine.

172
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:37,058
Tomorrow, I'll make a statement.

173
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:39,644
I'll go to the headquarters.

174
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:43,898
Once Russel and Patrick wake up,

175
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:46,484
I know they'll do the same.

176
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:48,361
They'll support you, too, sir.

177
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:56,911
- Thank you.
- Just watch your back, sir.

178
00:08:57,703 --> 00:08:59,997
Whoever is covering up the evidence…

179
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,165
[foreboding music playing]

180
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,167
…I'm sure they'll target you.

181
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:07,171
I can protect myself.

182
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:13,719
[music intensifying]

183
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:17,557
[unsettling music playing]

184
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,808
[elevator bell dings]

185
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:29,485
[Marcus] Sorry, sorry.

186
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:30,987
[announcement on PA system]
<i>Code blue! Code blue!</i>

187
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:33,114
<i>Dr. Daileg! Calling Dr. Daileg!</i>

188
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:36,826
<i>Please proceed to Room 203.</i>
<i>Patient Patrick Marquez.</i>

189
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:37,827
[suspenseful music playing]

190
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,787
<i>- Code blue! Code blue!</i>
- [hurried footsteps]

191
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:42,123
<i>Dr. Daileg! Calling Dr. Daileg!</i>

192
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:46,335
<i>Please proceed to Room 203.</i>
<i>Patient Patrick Marquez.</i>

193
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:55,511
- [monitor flatlining]
- [ambu bag hissing]

194
00:10:00,641 --> 00:10:03,728
[suspenseful music continues]

195
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,325
[tense music playing]

196
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:20,661
Patient SPO3 Patrick Marquez,
official time of death,

197
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:23,414
4:32 p.m.

198
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:34,675
[woman over PA system]
<i>Code blue! Code blue!</i>

199
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:37,720
<i>Patient Russel Contreras, Room 209!</i>

200
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,639
<i>Code blue! Code blue!</i>

201
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:42,391
<i>Patient Russel Contreras, Room 209!</i>

202
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:46,979
[tense music continues]

203
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:54,904
[Teresa] Two clear!

204
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:56,280
- Everybody, clear!
- [nurse] Clear!

205
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:57,865
[body thuds]

206
00:10:57,948 --> 00:11:01,410
[monitor flatlining]

207
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:07,708
[tense music continues]

208
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:16,425
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [heartbeat thumping rapidly]

209
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:20,304
[music becomes ominous]

210
00:11:22,431 --> 00:11:25,726
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [heart racing]

211
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,398
[tense music resumes]

212
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:35,152
[monitor flatlining]

213
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:45,371
[tense music continues]

214
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,289
[Marcus] <i>Sorry, sorry.</i>

215
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:50,584
Oliver…

216
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,508
[panicked breaths]

217
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:04,306
[tense music continues]

218
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:06,434
[breathing heavily]

219
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:18,028
[both grunting]

220
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,030
[grunting and groaning]

221
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,657
- [yells]
- [huffs]

222
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:23,409
[grunting]

223
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:25,286
[tense music continues]

224
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:26,370
[grunting and groaning]

225
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:29,206
[grunting and groaning]

226
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:31,625
[screaming in pain] Argh!

227
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:32,543
- [grunts]
- [whimpers]

228
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:35,671
[grunts and groans]

229
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:41,051
[both grunting]

230
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:45,556
[labored breathing, choking]

231
00:12:45,639 --> 00:12:46,682
- [grunts]
- [whimpers]

232
00:12:46,765 --> 00:12:47,975
[tense music continues]

233
00:12:48,058 --> 00:12:49,518
[groans]

234
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,314
[grunting and groaning]

235
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:55,691
[grunts]

236
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:57,151
[grunting and groaning]

237
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:58,903
[grunts]

238
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:00,279
[groans]

239
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:01,280
[panting]

240
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:02,406
- [kick lands]
- [grunts]

241
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:06,327
- [knife whooshing]
- [both huffing]

242
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:08,287
[tense music continues]

243
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:11,081
[grunting]

244
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:15,753
[flesh squelches]

245
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:16,837
Oliver!

246
00:13:17,671 --> 00:13:19,924
[muffled gunshots]

247
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:26,263
[tense music continues]

248
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:29,767
[grunting and groaning]

249
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,143
- [object shatters]
- [grunts]

250
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:35,773
[gunshot]

251
00:13:36,732 --> 00:13:37,816
[Marcus] Oliver--

252
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,151
Nurse!

253
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,862
Nurse, help!

254
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:46,575
- [oliver breathing raggedly]
- [morose music playing]

255
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:47,743
I'm sorry, sir.

256
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:49,537
[coughing]

257
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,539
I won't be able to testify…

258
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:52,873
so that we can right the wrong.

259
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,708
No. You're going to fight.

260
00:13:54,792 --> 00:13:56,001
Keep fighting.

261
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:57,795
You're going to live. Nurse!

262
00:13:57,878 --> 00:13:58,963
Nurse!

263
00:13:59,046 --> 00:14:02,174
- [groaning]
- [breathing heavily]

264
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:04,176
Sir…

265
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,345
Sir Marcus Reyes…

266
00:14:06,845 --> 00:14:09,974
[morose music continues]

267
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:13,102
It's my honor… serving with you, sir.

268
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,436
No. No.

269
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:16,772
You have to fight.

270
00:14:16,855 --> 00:14:19,358
You have to fight, Oliver. Hang in there!

271
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:21,402
Oliver… Oliver!

272
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,696
Help!

273
00:14:23,779 --> 00:14:25,322
Help!

274
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:29,076
[morose music continues]

275
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:32,788
Oliver!

276
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:34,999
Oliver!

277
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:39,545
[breathing heavily]

278
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:47,386
[dark music playing]

279
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:13,162
[footsteps approaching]

280
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:26,884
[camera shutter clicking]

281
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:35,225
[grim music playing]

282
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:49,740
[grim music continues]

283
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,590
[grim music continues]

284
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:14,890
[exhales heavily]

285
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,230
[grunting]

286
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,606
[yelling]

287
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:26,694
[breathing heavily]

288
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:32,616
[breathing heavily]

289
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:37,413
[phone ringing]

290
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:43,127
Marcus, they want you back at the office

291
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:45,379
before the media catches up
with you there.

292
00:16:45,462 --> 00:16:48,716
[grim music continues]

293
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,396
My teammates are gone.

294
00:17:04,314 --> 00:17:06,316
[morose music playing]

295
00:17:06,942 --> 00:17:09,111
[sobs] I couldn't protect them.

296
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:13,907
[exhales deeply]

297
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,410
My friends died because of me.

298
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:24,460
Son, their sacrifice won't be in vain.

299
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:26,795
I know you.

300
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:30,632
You will find justice for them.

301
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:36,013
Four of my teammates have already died.

302
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:40,476
Aren't you afraid for me?

303
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:44,271
I am.

304
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:46,523
But I know…

305
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:49,777
that's not what you need
to hear right now.

306
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:53,739
Just keep your promise to me, son.

307
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:56,533
That nothing bad will happen to you.

308
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:59,870
I can't bear to lose another son.

309
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,706
I'm begging you.

310
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:03,791
Please.

311
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:07,252
[Teresa sobbing]

312
00:18:07,336 --> 00:18:12,091
[morose music continues]

313
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:28,941
[unsettling music playing]

314
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:43,580
[Jalil groaning]

315
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:44,790
Jalil!

316
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:47,251
- [Jalil groaning]
- Jalil!

317
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:48,252
Mama!

318
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:50,295
- [woman] Jalil!
- [Jamillah sobbing]

319
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:53,757
Ma!

320
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:56,385
- [woman] Jalil!
- [groaning]

321
00:18:56,468 --> 00:19:00,389
[dramatic music playing]

322
00:19:00,472 --> 00:19:02,182
[woman in Arabic]
Praise and thanks be to Allah!

323
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:08,147
[Jamilah sighs]

324
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:16,989
[Jamillah sobbing]

325
00:19:17,072 --> 00:19:18,323
Jamillah.

326
00:19:25,205 --> 00:19:26,832
What happened?

327
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:35,424
[sobbing]

328
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:41,430
[dramatic music continues]

329
00:19:45,642 --> 00:19:47,811
[tense music]

330
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:50,856
[reporter] <i>The NLEA Chapel</i>
<i>is now open to the public</i>

331
00:19:50,939 --> 00:19:53,817
<i>for the fallen members</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha.</i>

332
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,694
Where's Father?

333
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:58,155
[Jamilah] <i>They arrested him.</i>
<i>He's been detained.</i>

334
00:19:58,238 --> 00:20:01,783
[Jalil] <i>Why do they have</i>
<i>to drag us into this?</i>

335
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,368
Why?!

336
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,412
He's their leader.

337
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:07,497
[reporter] Agent Reyes,
why did you order the killing

338
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:08,832
of children and women?

339
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,792
[Lara] <i>Marcus, get your head in the game.</i>

340
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:12,961
<i>If you really believe</i>
<i>you're being silenced,</i>

341
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,213
<i>then find out what the truth is…</i>

342
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,672
before you lose everything.

343
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:18,342
[Marcus] <i>My teammates were killed.</i>

344
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:21,094
But you have information on who did it.

345
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:26,141
I know someone silenced my team.

346
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:28,810
Tell me who it is! Tell me!

347
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:31,980
[activist] <i>Release Datu Rahman!</i>

348
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:36,318
We won't stop until we get justice!

349
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:37,736
You need to save Datu Rahman.

350
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:39,363
I'll fix all of this.

351
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:42,658
[Jalil] <i>I'm sure Father is innocent.</i>

352
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:44,660
[Jamilah] <i>Everyone thinks</i>
<i>you're already dead.</i>

353
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:49,873
[Jalil] <i>I won't stop</i>
<i>until I avenge our people.</i>

354
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:54,544
[music concludes]
